    <p class="description">The percentage of total market revenue or unit sales captured by one company. <strong>Formula: (Your revenue ÷ Total market revenue) × 100.</strong> A rising share means you are growing faster than the market. A falling share means competitors are winning, even if your revenue is up.</p>
